==Location and sets==
The major part of the movie was filmed at [[Dharavi]], [[Mumbai]], 
recreating the early 20th century [[Calcutta]].<ref 
name="bbc">{{cite 
news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/2119805.stm |title=No 
expense spared in Devdas remake |publisher=BBC News |date=12 July 2002 
|accessdate=2011-08-15}}</ref>  Chandramukhi's [[brothel|kotha]] was 
constructed next to an artificial lake, to make it look like a set in 
[[Benaras]] on the [[Ganges]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Indiatimes 
|url=http://devdas.indiatimes.com/sets.htm |title=India Times: Devdas:  The Making - Monuments and More - The Sets 
|publisher=Devdas.indiatimes.com |date= 
|accessdate=2011-06-30}}</ref> A temple city surrounded the set, 
for which inspiration was taken from the [[Dilwara Temples]] in 
[[Rajasthan]].<ref>{{cite 
web|url=http://www.indiatoday.com/itoday/20020520/cover.shtml 
|title=Devdas -Bollywood's Gamble |publisher=India Today |date=20 May 2002 |accessdate=2011-06-30}}</ref> For the creation of Paro's 
room in a [[haveli]] 12,20,00,008 pieces of stained glass were 
used.<ref>{{cite 
web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2002-05-01/mumbai/27121999_1_havelis-sets-devdas
 |title=Times of India: Dheeraj sets his sights on sets of Devdas 
|publisher=The Times of India |date=1 May 2002 
|accessdate=2011-06-30}}</ref> Additionally, there were a few 
accidents on set during the making, resulting in the death of 2
people.<ref>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KpVd97fucAs</ref>

