==Awards==
* ''Devdas'' was [[List of Indian submissions for Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|India's entry for Best Foreign Language Film at the Oscars]] in 2003.
* The film was also screened at the [[2002 Cannes Film Festival]],<ref name="festival-cannes.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/archives/ficheFilm/id/3150715/year/2002.html |title=Festival de Cannes: Devdas |accessdate=2009-11-03|work=festival-cannes.com}}</ref>

;[[Filmfare Awards]]
''Devdas'' won ten awards at the 2002 Filmfare Awards, and was the fourth film to win the four major awards (Best Movie, Best Director, Best Actor and Best Actress).
* [[Filmfare Best Movie Award|Best Film]] - Bharat Shah
* [[Filmfare Best Actor Award|Best Actor]] - Shahrukh Khan
* [[Filmfare Best Actress Award|Best Actress]] - Aishwarya Rai
* [[Filmfare Best Director Award|Best Director]] - Sanjay Leela Bhansali
* [[Filmfare Best Supporting Actress Award|Best Supporting Actress]] - Madhuri Dixit
* [[Filmfare Best Female Playback Award|Best Female Playback]] - Kavita Krishnamurthy & Shreya Ghosal for "[[Dola Re Dola]]"
* [[Filmfare Best Cinematographer Award|Best Cinematographer]] - [[Binod Pradhan]]
* [[Filmfare Best Art Direction|Best Art Direction]] - [[Nitin Chandrakant Desai]]
* [[Filmfare Best Choreography Award|Best Choreography]] - [[Saroj Khan]]
* [[Filmfare Best Scene of the Year Award|Best Scene of the Year]] - Confrontation scene between Parvati and Chandramukhi.

;[[National Film Award (India)|National Film Awards]]
''Devdas'' won five awards at the 2002 national awards:
* [[National Film Award for Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment]]
* [[National Film Award for Best Art Direction]]- [[Nitin Chandrakant Desai]]
* [[National Film Award for Best Female Playback Singer]] - [[Shreya Ghoshal]]
* [[National Film Award for Best Choreography]] - [[Saroj Khan]]
* [[National Film Award for Best Costume Design]] - [[Neeta Lulla]], Abu Jani, Sandeep Khosla and Reza Shariffi

;[[Star Screen Awards]]
''Devdas'' won five awards at the 2002 Star Screen Awards:
* Best Actor - [[Shahrukh Khan]] (shared with [[Ajay Devgan]])
* Best Actress - [[Aishwarya Rai]]
* Best Supporting Actress - [[Madhuri Dixit]]
* Star Screen Award Jodi No. 1 - [[Aishwarya Rai]] & [[Shahrukh Khan]]
* Star Screen Award Best Male Playback - [[Udit Narayan]] for "Woh Chand Jaisi Ladki"

;[[IIFA Awards]]
''Devdas'' won six awards at the 2003 IIFA Awards:
* [[IIFA Best Movie Award|Best Movie]] - ''Devdas'' - [[Bharat Shah]]
* [[IIFA Best Director Award]] - [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]]
* [[IIFA Best Actor Award|Best Actor]] In Leading Role [[Devdas]] - [[Shahrukh Khan]]
* [[IIFA Best Actress Award|Best Actress]] In Leading Role [[Devdas]] - [[Aishwarya Rai]]
* [[IIFA Best Supporting Actress Award|Best Actress in a Supporting Role]] [[Devdas]] - [[Kirron Kher]]
* [[IIFA Best Female Playback Award]] [[Devdas]] - [[Shreya Ghosal]], [[Kavita Krishnamurthy]] for [[Dola Re Dola]]

;[[MTV Asia Awards]]
''Devdas'' won the 2003 Asian Film Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/31/stories/2003013100910603.htm |title=The Hindu<U+00A0>: 2003 MTV Asia Awards |publisher=Hinduonnet.com |date=31 January 2003 |accessdate=2011-06-30}}{{dead link|date=February 2012}} {{wayback|df=yes|url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/31/stories/2003013100910603.htm}}{{dead link|date=February 2012}}</ref><ref>[http://game.mtvasia.com/News/200301/25002836.html]{{dead link|date=June 2011}} {{wayback|df=yes|url=http://game.mtvasia.com/News/200301/25002836.html}}</ref><ref>[http://www.blockbusteronline.com.mx/69775/dvd.aspx]{{dead link|date=June 2011}} {{wayback|df=yes|url=http://www.blockbusteronline.com.mx/69775/dvd.aspx}}</ref>

;[[British Academy Film Awards]]
''Devdas'' was nominated for the [[BAFTA Award for Best Film|BAFTA Award for Best Foreign Language Film]], 2003.

==Box office==
''Devdas''  grossed {{INRConvert|535|m}} and was declared an all time blockbuster at the Indian box office by [[Box Office India]].<ref>http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=208&catName=MjAwMg==</ref> The film was the highest grossing film of 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=208&catName=MjAwMg==
 |title=Box Office India 2002 |publisher=Boxofficeindia.com |date=23 March 1931 |accessdate=2011-06-30}}</ref> It grossed {{INRConvert|843.0|m}} worldwide.<ref 
name="wwbo">[http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=312&catName=TGlmZXRpbWU=  Boxofficeindia.com]</ref> When adjusted for inflation its total gross worldwide is {{INRConvert|1.55|b}}.
<ref name="boxofficeindia1">[http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=313&catName=TGlmZXRpbWUgQWRqdXN0ZWQ=  Boxofficeindia.com]</ref>
It opened strongly at multiplexes in Mumbai with a whopping 100% occupancy at theatres.

